From: Florian Eckert <fe@dev.tdt.de>
Date: Fri, 19 Dec 2025 09:17:18 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] x86/PCI: only define pci_domain_nr if target also has ACPI
 enabled

If the 'x86' target has 'PCI' then the config option 'CONFIG_PCI_DOMAINS'
is set. That means on 'x86' target the 'pci_domain_nr()' is visible for
the 'x86' target and the domain number can be read from sysdata. The
sysdata struct is filled by 'ACPI' through the function
'pci_acpi_scan_root()' during the scan. If an x86 system is used, this is
the normal procedure.

In my case, I am also using an 'x86' system, but the data for the
'pci_domain_nr' are provided by a 'DTS' and not from 'ACPI'. For this to
work, the 'CONFIG_PCI_DOMAINS_GENERIC' option must be enabled.

By enabling the option, the function is declared twice. Once in
'/include/linux/pci.h' and once in '/arch/x86/include/asm/pci.h' and
therefore causes a compilation error.

To fix this, the offended function in '/arch/x86/include/asm/pci.h' is
only enabled, if also the config option 'CONFIG_ACPI' is set. This change
makes it possible for 'x86' targets that do not have 'ACPI' but do have a
'DTS' to also provide the pci domain number via the 'DTS'.

Signed-off-by: Florian Eckert <fe@dev.tdt.de>
---
 arch/x86/include/asm/pci.h | 6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/x86/include/asm/pci.h b/arch/x86/include/asm/pci.h
index b3ab80a03365..89a14415c226 100644
--- a/arch/x86/include/asm/pci.h
+++ b/arch/x86/include/asm/pci.h
@@ -39,17 +39,19 @@ static inline struct pci_sysdata *to_pci_sysdata(const struct pci_bus *bus)
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_PCI
 
-#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_DOMAINS
+#if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_PCI_DOMAINS) && IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_ACPI)
 static inline int pci_domain_nr(struct pci_bus *bus)
 {
 	return to_pci_sysdata(bus)->domain;
 }
+#endif /* CONFIG_PCI_DOMAINS && CONFIG_ACPI */
 
+#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_DOMAINS
 static inline int pci_proc_domain(struct pci_bus *bus)
 {
 	return pci_domain_nr(bus);
 }
-#endif
+#endif /* CONFIG_PCI_DOMAINS */
 
 #ifdef CONFIG_PCI_MSI
 static inline void *_pci_root_bus_fwnode(struct pci_bus *bus)
